President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to appoint several individuals to key positions in his Administration. Monica Elizabeth Crowley, currently Senior Advisor for Public Affairs to the Secretary of the Treasury, is being considered for the role of Assistant Secretary of the Treasury (Public Affairs). Crowley has a background as a political and foreign affairs analyst on various media platforms, including Fox News, ABC News, and NBC News. She is also a bestselling author and opinion columnist. Scott Walker, former Governor of Wisconsin, is being nominated as a Member (Private Life) of the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars in the Smithsonian Institution. Upon appointment, Walker will also serve as Chair. Andrew Kerwin Maloney, from Virginia, is designated to be Vice Chair of the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars.